<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-568-058  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 568 058.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  June 11 1990 n594 p25(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Darpa seeks text-retrieval algorithms. (Defense Advanced ResearchProjects Agency)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Robinson, Brian.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>DARPA plans a four-year project to develop algorithms formultilingual text retrieval and translation, initially targetingautomatic input for large databases.andP;  The algorithms will detectdocuments on a given topic and automatically extract specific datafrom the documents.andP;  Main applications will be automatic routingof incoming documents and subsequent retrieval, then automaticdatabase filing.andP;  The algorithms must also be effective across awide range of free text, 'trainable', extensible by users ratherthan developers, portable across languages and applications, andcontaining all the levels of robustness and efficiency required ofall Department of Defense systems.andP;  Development of the algorithmswill occupy the first two years of the project, expected to costfrom $4 million to $5 million per year, while the remaining twoyears, yet to be funded, will focus on design of a user interfaceand construction of prototype systems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     AlgorithmsGovernment FundingResearch and DevelopmentDocument Management SystemsUnited States. Defense Advanced Research Projects AgencyPrototype.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>